[ProMED-mail is indebted to James Wilson on 2 counts. Firstly for his lucid account of the Black Canyon Infectious Disease Forecasting Station and its role in providing an operational forecasting system for the local and general community, exploiting the "One Health" philosophy.

Secondly, his surveillance activities have revealed that the clinical severity of the current seasonal outbreak of RSV infection in the USA may at least in part be a consequence of co-infection with other respiratory tract pathogens, of which the most important appears to be human metapneumovirus, and only rarely influenza virus. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1z-L.]
